'''''X-Wing Rogue Squadron'' 13''', also labeled as '''"The Warrior Princess, Chapter 1"''', is the thirteenth issue in the ''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Rogue Squadron]]'' series of comics. It was released on [[November 27]], [[1996]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''The squadron's roster has contained Corellian heroes and Alderaanian fighter aces, but when the royal court of Eiattu 6 comes to reclaim their princess from the ranks of Rogue Squadron, it's a surprise to everyone... especially the princess!''

==Plot summary==
In a [[Flight simulator/Legends|starfighter simulator]], [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] (in a simulated [[TIE Advanced x1/Legends|TIE Advanced]]) eliminates his squadmates one by one. After discussing their performances and acquainting each other with the squadron's new arrivals, the squadron disbands while Antilles and Tycho Celchu attend a mission briefing. [[Noble/Legends|Grand Duke]] [[Gror Pernon]] of [[Eiattu]] requests [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] to escort the world's rightful princess from [[Mrlsst/Legends|Mrlsst]] to Eiattu to stop the infighting between the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]], the noble-led faction of the [[Priamsta]] and the world's royal family, most of whom were said to be executed by the nobles, including the previous emperor and Pernon's brother, [[Antbbianplourr III|Antbbianplour III]]. 

When Antilles, Celchu and Pernon visit the Rogues' barracks, the Grand Duke identifies [[Isplourrdacartha Estillo|Plourr]] as "Princess Isplourrdacartha Estillo", causing Plour to knock him down, claiming that he had murdered her family. Pernon claims to have tried to stop the royal family's murder, which Plourr dismisses as a fairy tale. After tearfully reuniting with her childhood [[Nanny droid/Legends|nanny droid]] [[9-A9|9-A9 "Nynie"]], Plourr agrees to come to Eiattu upon learning that her brother and Eiattu's rightful ruler, [[Harrandatha Estillo (impostor)|Harran]], is alive. 

The Rogues attend Plourr's official return presentation as princess of Eiattu. Plourr's second cousin, [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Rial Pernon]], introduces himself as Plourr's future husband to the shock of Antilles and Celchu. 

